artifactory:index/getFileinfo:getFileinf.description:
## # Artifactory File Info Data Source

Provides an Artifactory fileinfo datasource. This can be used to read metadata of files stored in Artifactory repositories.

{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage
{{% example %}}

```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as artifactory from "@pulumi/artifactory";

// 
const my_file = pulumi.output(artifactory.getFileinfo({
    path: "/path/to/the/artifact.zip",
    repository: "repo-key",
}));
```
```python
import pulumi
import pulumi_artifactory as artifactory

my_file = artifactory.get_fileinfo(path="/path/to/the/artifact.zip",
    repository="repo-key")
```
```csharp
using Pulumi;
using Artifactory = Pulumi.Artifactory;

class MyStack : Stack
{
    public MyStack()
    {
        var my_file = Output.Create(Artifactory.GetFileinfo.InvokeAsync(new Artifactory.GetFileinfoArgs
        {
            Path = "/path/to/the/artifact.zip",
            Repository = "repo-key",
        }));
    }

}
